# /self-update

Updates the **ai-resources** repository (git pull), syncs **vendor** skill packs from `vendor-manifest.json`, and regenerates **`cursor/skills-registry.md`** + **`cursor/skills-index.json`**.

## When triggered

User says `/self-update` or runs **`agent-kit self-update`** from the repo.

## Command

```bash
export AGENT_KIT=/path/to/ai-resources   # optional if using repo bin/agent-kit
/path/to/ai-resources/bin/agent-kit self-update
```

With `AGENT_KIT` unset, `bin/agent-kit` sets it to the repository root automatically.

## Steps (what the CLI does)

1. **`git pull`** in **`$AGENT_KIT`** when `.git` exists.
2. **`vendor-sync`** — vendors → **`$AGENT_KIT/cursor/skills`**.
3. **`generate`** — registry + JSON index under **`cursor/`**.

## Adding vendors

Edit **`vendor-manifest.json`** at the repo root, then run **`agent-kit vendor-sync`**.

## `~/.cursor`

Rules/skills are **not** stored under `~/.cursor` anymore; they live in **`cursor/`** in this repo. A future **install** script will link into `~/.cursor` for Cursor.
